tence\": \"The Food Detectives  Europe's best food experts are joining forces to crack down on fraud.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Euronews is following them in this special series: The Food Detectives  Water Matters  Europe's water is under increasing pressure.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3160, \"end\": 3175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Food Detectives\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pollution, droughts, floods are taking their toll on our drinking water, lakes, rivers and coastlines.\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join us on a journey around Europe to see why protecting ecosystems matters, how our wastewater can be better managed, and to discover some of the best water solutions.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video reports, an animated explainer series and live debate - find out why Water Matters, from Euronews.\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3606, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Euronews\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climate Now  We give you the latest climate facts from the world's leading source, analyse the trends and explain how our planet is changing.\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We meet the experts on the front line of climate change who explore new strategies to mitigate and adapt.\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Olympics Games officially kicked off in France's capital, Paris, on Friday, drawing millions of athletes, spectators, and tourists from around the world.\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 4028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3915, \"end\": 3921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9982581553691133, \"rank\": 0.0012409501920058305, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3933, \"end\": 3938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996257429, \"rank\": 3.743822692887341e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The influx of visitors to this large-scale, global event has raised concerns about the potential spread of various illnesses, including mosquito-borne ones.\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One infection that has attracted significant attention recently is dengue fever due to a surge in cases over the past couple of months.\", \"from\": 4188, \"to\": 4323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dengue fever, which is not common in northern Europe, has started spreading within the continent due to local mosquitoes carrying the virus.\", \"from\": 4325, \"to\": 4465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There have also been registered cases of dengue fever in the Paris region.\", \"from\": 4467, \"to\": 4541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4528, \"end\": 4533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996257429, \"rank\": 3.743822692887341e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Dengue detectives\\\" were deployed in Paris ahead of the Olympics to keep an eye on Asian tiger mosquitoes, which feed on humans and spread the virus.\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4580, \"end\": 4585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996257429, \"rank\": 3.743822692887341e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4626, \"end\": 4648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian tiger mosquitoes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's true the Olympic Games are a critical moment.\", \"from\": 4694, \"to\": 4745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are prioritising our surveillance in places that will host large gatherings.\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is where risk of transmission is highest,\\\" C\\u00e9cile Somarriba, director of health monitoring and safety at the Greater Paris Regional Health Agency (ARS), told The Telegraph.\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 5003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4940, \"end\": 4953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9998819189103668, \"rank\": 0.00011809503420897878, \"text\": \"Greater Paris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_metropolitan_area\"}, {\"begin\": 4954, \"end\": 4976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regional_Health_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Regional Health Agency\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regional_Health_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regional_Health_Agency\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to health officials, 526 nesting traps are being checked for the presence of these dengue-carrying mosquitoes, with priority given to places expected to host large gatherings in an effort to limit the transmission risk.\", \"from\": 5005, \"to\": 5234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dengue fever, also known as break-bone fever, is transmitted to humans through the bite of infected mosquitoes.\", \"from\": 5236, \"to\": 5347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the World Health Organization (WHO), symptoms of infection include high fever, severe headaches, body aches, nausea, vomiting, and rash.\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These symptoms typically occur four to 10 days after infection.\", \"from\": 5500, \"to\": 5563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the symptoms usually improve within one to two weeks, some individuals might develop severe dengue, which can be fatal in extreme cases.\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, many dengue infections are asymptomatic or result in only mild illness.\", \"from\": 5709, \"to\": 5787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Given the heightened alert and registered cases in the Paris region, those attending the event need to take precautions to avoid getting infected, officials have said.\", \"from\": 5789, \"to\": 5956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5844, \"end\": 5849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996257429, \"rank\": 3.743822692887341e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the best way to prevent dengue fever is by avoiding mosquito bites, there issome WHO-recommended adviceto follow to protect against dengue.\", \"from\": 5958, \"to\": 6103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6016, \"end\": 6024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.901732787155048e-22, \"text\": \"mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wear protective clothing:Choose long-sleeved shirts, long pants, socks, and shoes to cover as much of the body as possible.\", \"from\": 6105, \"to\": 6228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Use mosquito repellents:Apply insect repellents containing DEET, Picaridin or IR3535 to exposed skin and clothing.\", \"from\": 6230, \"to\": 6344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Use screen windows:Ensure that windows and doors are properly screened to keep mosquitoes out.\", \"from\": 6346, \"to\": 6440, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Use mosquito coils and vaporizers:These could be particularly effective in reducing mosquito populations indoors.\", \"from\": 6442, \"to\": 6555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, if infection still occurs, people are recommended to rest, drink plenty of liquids, and use paracetamol for pain relief.\", \"from\": 6559, \"to\": 6688, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In cases where the infection is severe, it is crucial to contact your doctor and seek care in hospitals as soon as possible.\", \"from\": 6690, \"to\": 6814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Browse today's tags\", \"from\": 6820, \"to\": 6839, \"entities\": []}]}"